The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                Eastern Railway will run 78 special trains from May 2 to June 16 to cater to the summer rush. Twenty-six trains will run between Sealdah and Delhi, 12 between Sealdah and Hardwar, 14 between Sealdah and Gorakhpur, 12 between Howrah and New Jalpaiguri and 14 between Howrah and Kathgodam.    Amar Golder, 52, hanged himself from a tree near his Netaji Pally home late on Thursday. Son Suvajit lodged a police complaint alleging that some members of a local club had accused him of theft and beaten him up on Wednesday. A probe revealed Amar had two wives and been suffering from depression because of a family discord.    City models Jessica, Tina, Neeraj and Sreshtha and actress Rimjhim will participate in a walk on Saturday to spread awareness about diabetes along with patients and others. The walk will begin at Menoka cinema at 10am and end at the TakeCare Diabetes Speciality Centre on Rashbehari Avenue, where free blood sugar tests will be conducted. The speciality centre was set up by Elbit Healthcare Pvt Ltd of Israel and is affiliated to The Whittier Institute for Diabetes.    Gariahat police have started a case of negligence against the caretaker of a building in connection with the death of mechanic Krishanu Nashkar last Friday. Nashkar was standing on the roof of an elevator and fixing a snag when he was crushed to death after he lost his balance.    Thieves broke into a cellphone shop in Shyamnagar on Thursday night and decamped with cellphones and recharge vouchers worth nearly Rs 1 lakh.                                                                                                                                                                   
